\f2\b \cf0 \strokec2 The texts as anti-amnesia technology.
\f0\b0 \
This reframes the entire enterprise. Not primitive cosmology. Not bronze-age power consolidation dressed as divine command. But something more like a 
\f2\b civilizational dead man's switch
\f0\b0  \'97 written by people who had seen enough of the cycle to recognize it, who understood that the recognition itself wouldn't survive unaided across generational timescales, and who encoded the pattern into the most durable transmission medium available to them: sacred text.\
Sacred 
\f3\i specifically because
\f0\i0  the sacred is the only category human civilizations have consistently refused to let die. You can burn a library. You cannot easily burn what a people believes God said.\
The sophistication hypothesis \'97 that these weren't primitive people fumbling toward truth but 
\f3\i pattern-recognizing minds
\f0\i0  encoding hard-won civilizational intelligence into a format robust enough to outlast the amnesia \'97 is actually more parsimonious than the condescension of modernity. It requires fewer assumptions. These were humans. Humans who had watched empires rise and collapse. Who had lived through their own OT/NT oscillations at smaller scales. Who may have understood, with terrible clarity, exactly what they were trying to prevent.\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf4 \strokec4 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f2\b \cf0 \strokec2 The amnesiac species problem.
\f0\b0 \
This is the crux that makes the exit condition so difficult. The loop persists not because humans are evil, but because 
\f2\b wisdom doesn't inherit biologically.
\f0\b0  Every generation is, in a meaningful sense, born pre-civilizational. The entire apparatus of culture, religion, law, and education exists to re-install in 20 years what took millennia to accumulate. And it does so imperfectly. Every time.\
The texts were an attempt to solve this. And they 
\f3\i partially
\f0\i0  worked \'97 they've carried the pattern recognition further forward than any purely oral or institutional transmission could have. But they also got captured. Weaponized. Became frames in the very cycle they were meant to interrupt.\
Which suggests the medium, however sophisticated, was still insufficient. The encoding survived. The 
\f3\i meaning
\f0\i0  kept getting lost inside new OT phases that wore the text as uniform rather than reading it as warning.\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf4 \strokec4 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f2\b \cf0 \strokec2 The Human Unification Event as exit condition.
\f0\b0 \
What's elegant about this formulation is its deliberate under-specification. You're not prescribing the mechanism \'97 ideology, technology, existential threat, spiritual breakthrough \'97 because to prescribe the mechanism is to immediately fracture along the lines of 
\f3\i which
\f0\i0  mechanism, 
\f3\i whose
\f0\i0  unification, 
\f3\i on what terms.
\f0\i0  Every previous attempt at unification has failed precisely by over-specifying: unify under Rome, under Christ, under the Caliphate, under liberal democracy, under the proletariat.\
The definition you offer \'97 
\f3\i whatever it takes to unify without corrupting or re-fracturing
\f0\i0  \'97 is almost a 
\f2\b negative definition.
\f0\b0  It describes the exit condition by its structural properties rather than its content. Which is arguably the only honest way to define it from inside the loop.\
The thermostat catching the house on fire is not metaphorical at this point. The ceiling of each OT phase scales with technology. We are now in a civilizational moment where the next full OT phase \'97 conducted with current and near-future weapons \'97 plausibly ends the experiment entirely. The loop that was sustainable at Bronze Age kill-ceilings, that was terrible but survivable at WWII scale, is approaching a threshold where 
\f2\b the oscillation amplitude exceeds the system's ability to restabilize.
\f0\b0 \
The ancients couldn't have known the specific mechanism. But the structure of their warning \'97 
\f3\i this pattern, uninterrupted, ends badly
\f0\i0  \'97 was exactly correct.\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf4 \strokec4 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f2\b \cf0 \strokec2 Where I think the genuine difficulty lives:
\f0\b0 \
The unification event, by your own definition, cannot be imposed. Imposed unification is just another OT phase in better clothing \'97 Rome called it 
\f3\i Pax
\f0\i0 , the British called it 
\f3\i civilization
\f0\i0 , the Americans called it 
\f3\i the rules-based international order.
\f0\i0  Each was a unification attempt that contained within it the fracture lines of the next cycle.\
So the exit condition seems to require something that has never yet existed: 
