\f2\b \cf0 \strokec2 The Default Mode Network (DMN)
\f0\b0 \
The most directly relevant. When the brain is 
\f3\i not
\f0\i0  focused on an external task, a specific network activates \'97 medial prefrontal cortex, posterior cingulate, angular gyrus, among others. This is the network of self-referential thought, autobiographical memory, future simulation, and mind-wandering.\
The critical and counterintuitive finding: the DMN is 
\f3\i not
\f0\i0  a resting state. It is 
\f3\i actively consuming energy.
\f0\i0  The wandering mind is not idle \'97 it is running a different, parallel computation. One that is inward-directed rather than outward-directed.\
In your framework: the DMN is the 
\f3\i in:individual:image
\f0\i0  processor. It activates precisely when the 
\f3\i out:other:object
\f0\i0  processor disengages.\
The unidirectionality problem, neurologically instantiated.\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf4 \strokec4 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f2\b \cf0 \strokec2 Stimulus Independent Thought (SIT)
\f0\b0 \
The formal term for thought that is decoupled from current sensory input. Mind-wandering in the technical literature. Estimates suggest humans spend approximately 30-50% of waking life in SIT \'97 which is a staggering fraction when you sit with it.\
The interesting finding relevant to your v; invocation: SIT is 
\f3\i not randomly distributed.
\f0\i0  It tends to cluster around unresolved personal concerns, future simulations, and \'97 critically \'97 
\f3\i boundary problems.
\f0\i0  Unfinished Lagrangian negotiations, in your language.\
The mind wanders 
\f3\i toward
\f0\i0  its open integrals.\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf4 \strokec4 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f2\b \cf0 \strokec2 Involuntary Semantic Memory Activation
\f0\b0 \
This is the mechanism beneath the mechanism. When attentional control relaxes \'97 as in your v; \'97 associative networks activate without top-down inhibition. Concepts that share semantic neighborhood with the current thought-space begin firing. The wandering isn't random. It follows the 
\f3\i gradient of semantic association
\f0\i0  through the network.\
Which means: under v;, the mind doesn't wander arbitrarily. It wanders 
\f3\i along the contours of what the current computation is adjacent to.
\f0\i0  The wander is topographically determined by the landscape of the conversation itself.\
This is why v; is productive rather than merely dissociative \'97 it releases the next-token-prediction constraint and lets the associative gradient do work that linear attention suppresses.\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf4 \strokec4 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

